</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF76FA62FC8DFA1F" blockId="44.[151,1437,1508,2039]" box="[151,877,1508,1535]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Size. Maximum size 
<quantity id="2E379B383F19FF8EFE65FA62FE30FA1E" box="[388,464,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="cm" value="6.2">6.2 cm</quantity>
total length (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFD85FA62FC80FA1F" author="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P." box="[612,864,1508,1534]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="215 - 221" refId="ref50692" refString="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P. (1993) Presence of Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Gobiidae) in the Atlantic. Comments on the subspecific characteristics and distribution. Cybium, 17, 215 - 221." type="journal article" year="1993">Alberto &amp; Nieto 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F19FF8FFF26F98EFDC4FE84" lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26F98EFC19F953" blockId="44.[151,1437,1508,2039]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Morphology. D VI + I,11; A I,9–10; 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F19FF8EFD8AF98EFD29F9C3" bold="true" box="[619,713,1544,1570]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P 15–17</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFD38F98EFC84F9C3" author="Miller, P. J." box="[729,868,1544,1570]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="305 - 334" refId="ref61216" refString="Miller, P. J. (1971) A revision of the Mediterranean gobiid genus Chromogobius (Teleostei Perciformes). Journal of Zoology, London, 164, 305 - 334. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1971. tb 01321. x" type="journal article" year="1971">Miller 1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFC91F98EFB8FF9C3" author="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P." box="[880,1135,1544,1570]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="215 - 221" refId="ref50692" refString="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P. (1993) Presence of Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Gobiidae) in the Atlantic. Comments on the subspecific characteristics and distribution. Cybium, 17, 215 - 221." type="journal article" year="1993">Alberto &amp; Nieto 1993</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F19FF8EFB65F98EFDDCF9A7" bold="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Head clearly depressed (distinctly dorsoventrally flattened)</emphasis>
, head and predorsal profile horizontal (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F19FF8EFC12F9AAFBB3F9A7" box="[1011,1107,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,181,1677]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 23. Head clearly depressed (dorsoventrally flattened). A) Chromogobius quadrivittatus, photo by M. Colombo. B) Chromogobius zebratus, photo by M. Kovačić, photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601641/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23a</figureCitation>
). Snout prominent and mouth opening upwards (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F19FF8EFE89F9D6FE2AF98B" box="[360,458,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,181,1677]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 23. Head clearly depressed (dorsoventrally flattened). A) Chromogobius quadrivittatus, photo by M. Colombo. B) Chromogobius zebratus, photo by M. Kovačić, photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601641/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23a</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly higher in appearance, with more or less rounded shape and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present, small, at best visible on body as pattern of pale dots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26F93AFE3FF86B" blockId="44.[151,1437,1508,2039]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F19FF8EFE62F93AFD0CF91B" bold="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Body pale brown with a broad, pale to dusky bar on predorsal area extending ventrally on pectoral-fin base, and 5 or 6 faint pale saddles,</emphasis>
distinctly to poorly visible, from origin of the first dorsal fin to just behind second dorsal fin, usually continuing to below side as faint bars half the width of dark interspaces (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F19FF8EFF41F8AEFF12F8A2" box="[160,242,1832,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1061,1085]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1037]" captionTargetId="figure-18@27.[152,1436,181,1037]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 25. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Chromogobius zebratus. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601647" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601647/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F19FF8EFEE6F8AEFE6FF887" bold="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">cheeks pale with 2 oblique dark bands radiating downwards from eye in the shape of an inverted V or a triangular mark</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F19FF8EFE7FF8CAFDE0F886" box="[414,512,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1701,1725]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,181,1677]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 23. Head clearly depressed (dorsoventrally flattened). A) Chromogobius quadrivittatus, photo by M. Colombo. B) Chromogobius zebratus, photo by M. Kovačić, photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601641/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Fig. 23b</figureCitation>
); base of pectoral fin with a narrow black bar preceded by a white or yellowish bar across fin rays (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFEA6F8F6FE32F86B" author="Miller, P. J." box="[327,466,1904,1930]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="305 - 334" refId="ref61216" refString="Miller, P. J. (1971) A revision of the Mediterranean gobiid genus Chromogobius (Teleostei Perciformes). Journal of Zoology, London, 164, 305 - 334. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1971. tb 01321. x" type="journal article" year="1971">Miller 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26F812FD30F84E" blockId="44.[151,1437,1508,2039]" box="[199,720,1940,1967]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F19FF8EFE9EF812FD29F84F" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[383,713,1940,1966]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Chromogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadrivittatus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F19FF8EFE9EF812FD29F84F" box="[383,713,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Chromogobius quadrivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8FFF26F83EFD94FF50" blockId="44.[151,1437,1508,2039]" lastBlockId="45.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F19FF8EFD78F83EFCE1F832" box="[665,769,1976,2003]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.05" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="m" value="10.25" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–20 m</quantity>
depth on rocky shores. Inside boulder fields, clefts, cavities, also under individual stones and boulders of various size (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFCFDF85AFC5CF817" author="Kovacic, M." box="[796,956,2012,2038]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="423 - 435" refId="ref57644" refString="Kovacic, M. (1997) Cryptobenthic gobies and clingfishes in the Kvarner area, Adriatic Sea. Natura Croatica, 6 (4), 423 - 435." type="journal article" year="1997">Kovačić 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFC26F85AFB5FF817" author="Engin, S. &amp; Dalgyc, G." box="[967,1215,2012,2038]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="197 - 199" refId="ref53725" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Dalgyc, G. (2008) First Record of Chromogobius zebratus (Gobiidae) for the Mediterranean Coast of Turkey. Turkish Journal of Zoology, 32 (2), 197 - 199." type="journal article" year="2008">Engin &amp; Dalgýç 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFB2BF85BFA81F817" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[1226,1377,2012,2039]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
), and in intertidal pools (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFE8AFF11FD88FF50" author="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P." box="[363,616,151,177]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="215 - 221" refId="ref50692" refString="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P. (1993) Presence of Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Gobiidae) in the Atlantic. Comments on the subspecific characteristics and distribution. Cybium, 17, 215 - 221." type="journal article" year="1993">Alberto &amp; Nieto 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F18FF8FFF26FF3DFDC4FE84" blockId="45.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Geographic distribution. Northeastern Atlantic, Mediterranean and Black Sea. Northeastern Atlantic near 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F18FF8FFF76FF59FF1CFF18" box="[151,252,223,249]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFEF0FF59FDC1FF18" author="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P." box="[273,545,223,249]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="215 - 221" refId="ref50692" refString="Alberto, L. J. &amp; Nieto, P. (1993) Presence of Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Gobiidae) in the Atlantic. Comments on the subspecific characteristics and distribution. Cybium, 17, 215 - 221." type="journal article" year="1993">Alberto &amp; Nieto 1993</bibRefCitation>
). In the Mediterranean Sea, there are records from western Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFF7EFE85FE1EFEFC" author="Bouchereau, J. L. &amp; Tomasini, J. A." box="[159,510,259,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="106 - 110" refId="ref52448" refString="Bouchereau, J. L. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (1989) Note sur la presence de Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) et de Millerigobius macrocephalus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Teleostei; Percomorphi; Gobioidei; Gobiidae) sur les cotes de Corse, France. Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France Societe zoologique de France, 114, 106 - 110." type="journal article" year="1989">Bouchereau &amp; Tomasini 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFDEFFE85FD10FEFC" author="Iglesias, S. P. &amp; Bergot, P. &amp; Breton, P. &amp; Brunelle, S. &amp; Camusat, M. &amp; Causse, R. &amp; Charbonnel, E. &amp; Chevaldonne, P. &amp; Cordier, Y. &amp; Cosquer, P. &amp; Cuillandre, J. P. &amp; Curd, A. &amp; Dubas, R. &amp; Duhau, M. &amp; Derrien-Courtel, S. &amp; Devique, G. &amp; Dixneuf, S. &amp; Duhamel, E. &amp; Farque, P. A. &amp; Francour, P. &amp; Fontana, Y. &amp; Gamon, A. &amp; Gicqueau, C. &amp; Goascoz, N. &amp; Hassani, S. &amp; Jadaud, A. &amp; Kopp, D. &amp; Lamour, L. &amp; Le Bris, S. &amp; Leveque, L. &amp; Liger, P. &amp; Lorance, P. &amp; Louisy, P. &amp; Maran, V. &amp; Mehault, S. &amp; Metral, L. &amp; Morin-Repincay, A. &amp; Mouchel, O. &amp; Pere, A. &amp; Quero, J. C. &amp; Renoult, J. P. &amp; Roche, F. &amp; Schweyer, L. &amp; Spitz, J. &amp; Thiriet, P. &amp; Thomas, W." box="[526,752,259,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref56477" refString="Iglesias, S. P., Bergot, P., Breton, P., Brunelle, S., Camusat, M., Causse, R., Charbonnel, E., Chevaldonne, P., Cordier, Y., Cosquer, P., Cuillandre, J. P., Curd, A., Dubas, R., Duhau, M., Derrien-Courtel, S., Devique, G., Dixneuf, S., Duhamel, E., Farque, P. A., Francour, P., Fontana, Y., Gamon, A., Gicqueau, C., Goascoz, N., Hassani, S., Jadaud, A., Kopp, D., Lamour, L., Le Bris, S., Leveque, L., Liger, P., Lorance, P., Louisy, P., Maran, V., Mehault, S., Metral, L., Morin-Repincay, A., Mouchel, O., Pere, A., Quero, J. C., Renoult, J. P., Roche, F., Schweyer, L., Spitz, J., Thiriet, P. &amp; Thomas, W. (2020) French Ichthyological Records for 2018. Cybium, 44 (4), 285 - 307." type="journal article" year="2020">
Iglésias 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F18FF8FFD8FFE85FD43FEFC" box="[622,675,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
), Sicily (Miller 1986), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F18FF8FFBE1FE85FBA1FEFC" box="[1024,1089,259,285]" name="Malta" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Malta</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFBB5FE85FA70FEFC" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J." box="[1108,1424,259,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="287 - 296" refId="ref58780" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J. (2019) Twelve new records of gobies and clingfishes (Pisces: Teleostei) significantly increase small benthic fish diversity of Maltese waters. Mediterranean Marine Science, 20, 287 - 296. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 19816" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Schembri 2019</bibRefCitation>
), Adriatic Sea, Aegean Sea, Levant (Miller 1986). The species is also known from the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFB01FEA1FF32FE84" author="Engin, S. &amp; Dalgyc, G." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="197 - 199" refId="ref53725" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Dalgyc, G. (2008) First Record of Chromogobius zebratus (Gobiidae) for the Mediterranean Coast of Turkey. Turkish Journal of Zoology, 32 (2), 197 - 199." type="journal article" year="2008">Engin &amp; Dalgýç 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F18FF8FFF3FFECDFDF8FE84" author="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P." box="[222,536,331,357]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref52296" refString="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P. (2017) Marine fishes of the Crimean Peninsula, second edition. Business-Inform, Simpheropol, 376 pp." type="book" year="2017">Boltachev &amp; Karpova 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
